
======================================================================
  PART 1: G₁₁ ≡ Fib (mod 5) — PROOF
======================================================================

Fibonacci: f(n) = f(n-1) + 1·f(n-2), roots in Q(√5)
G₁₁:      g(n) = g(n-1) + 11·g(n-2), roots in Q(√5)

Both sequences satisfy the SAME recurrence modulo 5!
Because 11 ≡ 1 (mod 5), so:
  g(n) = g(n-1) + 11·g(n-2) ≡ g(n-1) + 1·g(n-2) = f(n) (mod 5)

PROOF: If a(n) = a(n-1) + c·a(n-2) with a(0)=0, a(1)=1,
and b(n) = b(n-1) + c'·b(n-2) with b(0)=0, b(1)=1,
then c ≡ c' (mod p) implies a(n) ≡ b(n) (mod p) for all n.
Here c=1, c'=11, p=5, and 11 ≡ 1 (mod 5). QED.

All x ≡ 1 (mod 5) give G_x ≡ Fib (mod 5):
  x=  1 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]
  x=  6 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]
  x= 11 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]
  x= 16 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]
  x= 21 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]
  x= 31 (x mod 5 = 1): [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0]

x ≡ 2 (mod 5) gives G_x ≡ Jacobsthal (mod 5):
  x=  2 (x mod 5 = 2): [1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3]
  x=  7 (x mod 5 = 2): [1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3]
  x= 12 (x mod 5 = 2): [1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3]
  x= 17 (x mod 5 = 2): [1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3, 0, 1, 1, 3]

MOD-5 CLASSES:
  x ≡ 0 (mod 5): f(n) = f(n-1) + 0 → f(n) = 1 for all n (trivial)
  x ≡ 1 (mod 5): Fibonacci pattern (Pisano period 20 mod 5)
  x ≡ 2 (mod 5): Jacobsthal pattern
  x ≡ 3 (mod 5): x=3 pattern
  x ≡ 4 (mod 5): x=4 pattern
  x ≡ 0 (mod 5): Pisano period mod 5 = 1, pattern = [1]
  x ≡ 1 (mod 5): Pisano period mod 5 = 20, pattern = [1, 1, 2, 3, 0, 3, 3, 1, 4, 0, 4, 4, 3, 2, 0, 2, 2, 4, 1, 0]
  x ≡ 2 (mod 5): Pisano period mod 5 = 4, pattern = [1, 1, 3, 0]
  x ≡ 3 (mod 5): Pisano period mod 5 = 24, pattern = [1, 1, 4, 2, 4, 0, 2, 2, 3, 4, 3, 0, 4, 4, 1, 3, 1, 0, 3, 3, 2, 1, 2, 0]
  x ≡ 4 (mod 5): Pisano period mod 5 = 6, pattern = [1, 1, 0, 4, 4, 0]

